      • findJobsByAccountAndProduct

        IQueryBeanResult<Job> findJobsByAccountAndProduct(Account account,
                                                  java.lang.Boolean closed,
                                                  Job jobType,
                                                  Product product,
                                                  User user)
        Returns all jobs of a given type associated with the given account.
        Parameters:
        account - the account the job must be associated with
        closed - null if you don't care, true for only complete jobs, false for only incomplete jobs
        jobType - the type of job that must be matched, or null for all job types
        product - the product to which the job must refer, or null for any product type
        user - the user whose permissions will be used, or null to ignore permissions
        Returns:
        all jobs of the given type, on the given account, of the given product, that match the completeness requirement
